This paper investigates how to engage users, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The study involves analyzing how people and algorithms rank the surprisingness of facts, which is a task that can be approached using natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of computational models to induce surprise in humans, which is a topic related to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
